								<div class="text">
									<p>
										Ludhiana has a strong textile industry, known for cotton garments, hosiery, and fabric production. Many small and large businesses here are now using fabric printing machines to print on textiles directly. These machines help print designs, logos, and patterns on t-shirts, bedsheets, and other fabric products.
										This guide explains the types of textile printing machines available in Ludhiana, how they work, how much they cost, and what to check before buying one.

									</p>
									<h3>Common Types of Fabric Printing Machines in Ludhiana</h3>
									<p>
										Different machines are used depending on the fabric type, print size, and quantity. Here are the main options:
									</p>
									<h6>1. Digital Textile Printer</h6>
									<p>A digital textile printer prints directly from a computer file onto the fabric. It uses inkjet printheads and is used for smaller quantities or more detailed designs.</p>
									<h6>Used for:</h6
										<p>Custom t-shirts</p>
										<p>Scarves</p>
										<p>Bedsheets</p>
										<p>Fabric samples</p>
									<h3>2. Industrial Fabric Printing Machine</h3>
									<p>
										An industrial fabric printer is larger and faster. It’s used by manufacturers printing large amounts of fabric every day. These are common in Ludhiana’s factories and mills.
									</p>
									<h3>Used for:</h3>
									<p>Garment fabric</p>
									<p>Home textiles</p>
									<p>Uniforms</p>
									
									<h3>3. Pigment-Based Digital Fabric Printer</h3>
									<p>
										This machine prints directly onto cotton fabric using pigment ink. It doesn’t require steaming or washing after printing, which saves time and space.
									</p>
									<h3>Used for:</h3>
									<p>Tote bags</p>
									<p>Cotton shirts</p>
									<p>Printed tablecloths</p>
									<h3>4. Sublimation Printer</h3>
									<p>Sublimation printers are used to print on polyester fabric. The print is first transferred to paper, then heat is applied to move the image to the fabric.</p>
								   <h3>Used for:</h3>
								   <p>Sportswear</p>
								   <p>School uniforms</p>
								   <p>Promotional fabric</p>
								   <h3>How Fabric Printing Machines Work</h3>
								   <p>A typical fabric printing machine follows this basic process:</p>
								  <p>1. Load the design into the software</p
									  <p>2. Prepare the fabric (if required)</p>
									  <p>3. Feed the fabric into the machine</p>
									  <p>4. The printer applies ink to the fabric using printheads</p>
									  <p>5. The fabric passes through a dryer or heat press to fix the ink</p>
								     <p>Machines like the Ricoh Gen6 fabric printer are used in Ludhiana for high-speed printing with clear image quality.</p>
